headline: ODFL Q3 Deep Dive: Volume Weakness Persists, Cost Control and Network Positioning Take Focus
summary: Freight carrier Old Dominion (NASDAQ:ODFL) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales fell by 4.3% year on year to $1.41 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.28 per share was 5.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
